<title>USA: Patriot American buys 4 Ohio hotels.</title>
<headline>Patriot American buys 4 Ohio hotels.</headline>
<dateline>DALLAS 1997-07-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Patriot American Hospitality Inc said Wednesday its joint venture with Snavely Group completed the acquisition of four full-service hotels in Ohio.</p>
<p>Three of the hotels are in Cleveland, with the other in Akron, Patriot American said in a statement.</p>
<p>Patriot invested 90 percent and the Snavely Group invested 10 percent in the $51 million acquisition of the four properties, which includes the assumption of a $5.825 million first mortgage loan on the Radisson Beachwood in Cleveland.</p>
<p>Lattin said the company is evaluating opportunities to convert one or more of the acquired properties to one of the Wyndham brands.</p>
